      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Federal union No. 222 last night\nasked the Central Labor union to\nindorse its application to the Amer\nlean Federation of Labor for a char\nter for common labor such as pick\nand shovel men and hammer and\ndrill men. The request was grant\ned and the application with the in\ndorsement will be forwarded to the\nAmerican Federation of Labor at\nonce. Organizer Anderson of No\n222 said all his union desired to\ncontrol or organize was common\nlabor and they desired a charter for\nthat class of workmen. If the char\nter is granted this will end the\nstrife which has existed between\nthe two local federal unions and\nwill remove a cause of worry to all\ninterested in the advancement of\nwage workers."
    }
  ]
